The paper deals with the issue of pilot contamination in a massive MIMO OFDM system, which is a topic of interest in the fields of information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), signal processing (cs.SI), multimedia (cs.MM), and communication (cs.COM). The paper proposes a new approach to mitigate pilot contamination by aligning the power-delay profiles (PDP) of different users served by one base station (BS) and different BSs, which can be applied in various CS sub-categories. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT, followed by cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.MM, and cs.COM.
